We’ve been having some issues as of late with some of our parallel command groups seemingly not ending commands.

For example, we run the command below, and all the motors stop when the command ends, but the LEDs don’t.
This issue persists in some of our autons, where the command says it isn’t running in smartdashboard, but the next command in the auton can’t run, presumably because a command is already running with the same subsystems

Here’s an example:
We run this auton listed below:

image961×882 79.8 KB

However, when we actually run the auton, it looks like this:

The robot doesn’t shoot at the highlighted orange event marker in the first image, nor the next intake.
Our shooting command inside of PP looks like this:

image829×516 7.34 KB

(We did end the auton a little early after we saw it didn’t shoot or intake)

Any ideas or help would be very much appreciated!

Parallel commands groups end when all commands inside it have finished. It looks like all the commands in your screenshot have isFinished always returning false, so it will not end. You will have to figure out the conditional of when to return true for each command.

Xactlysharp:

LEDs don’t

My team’s LEDs don’t stop doing what they last were commanded to do. Maybe yours don’t either. If you want them to change to black or to another color then command them at the end of the previous command or do so in a default command that includes the LEDs.
